cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image classification tasks, specifically focusing on the bias towards recognizing textures rather than shapes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the robustness of CNN models, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of Universal Adversarial Perturbations (UAPs) to evaluate and compare the models' robustness suggests the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the limitations of the models and the need for further research, which could fall under the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
